The Vice President, along with a bipartisan group of mayors, discussed the challenges and solutions facing the country during a meeting. The Vice President thanked the mayors for their leadership and highlighted their role in making things work on the ground. She mentioned the passage of the American Rescue Plan and the Child Tax Credit as examples of their accomplishments. The Vice President then introduced the Build Back Better Agenda, which aims to combat the climate crisis, create better jobs, improve access to healthcare, and help families. She emphasized the importance of bipartisan cooperation in achieving these goals. The Vice President acknowledged the urgency of the moment and the need for transformative change, given the profound crisis and fractures in the system. She expressed gratitude to the mayors and looked forward to continuing their partnership.